   DETROIT -- Honda Motor Co. plans to introduce next fall a
subcompact that will get up to 65 miles per gallon in highway
driving -- the highest fuel economy ever recorded in the U.S.
   But for all of its expected efficiency, the new Honda
Civic Hatchback VX may wind up as more of a public relations
tool than a sales success. Highly fuel efficient cars such as
Honda's current CRX HF model or General Motors Corp.'s Geo
Metro XFi, which is the most efficient car on the road today,
